{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"alias":"medium-monogamous-dotterel","description":"Route the existing criterion->authoring mapping to plan authors, and fix the gate doc's stale threshold numbers. Docs-only change (no runtime behavior).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] CLAUDE.md's \"Ticket template the gates enforce\" section gains a paragraph directing authors, BEFORE writing a plan, to docs/plan-review-criteria-guide.md and `rebar explain <criterion-id>`, and names the current blocking-tier criterion ids (F1, E2, G5, T5e, COH, G6, T1, T4, T8, G1G2, E4) so authors know which sections to read first. Oracle: `grep -n \"plan-review-criteria-guide\" CLAUDE.md` and `grep -n \"rebar explain\" CLAUDE.md` each return at least one hit inside that section.\n- [ ] docs/plan-review-gate.md no longer states 0.70 as the block threshold for the calibration-2 criteria; its threshold statements match src/rebar/llm/plan_review/criteria_routing.json (0.60 for F1/E2/G5/T5e/COH/G6; 0.70 for T1/T4/T8/G1G2; 0.75 for E4). Oracle: `grep -n \"0\\.70\" docs/plan-review-gate.md` shows no line describing F1/E2/G5/T5e/COH/G6 at 0.70.\n- [ ] docs/plan-review-gate.md documents (one short paragraph) that remediation-mode eligibility currently requires a prior certified PASS signature, so the rising floor does not engage during BLOCK loops - the honest current behavior, cross-referencing the floor-eligibility story in this epic.\n- [ ] `make lint` passes (docs changes only; lint covers formatting of any touched files).\n\nFiles: CLAUDE.md, docs/plan-review-gate.md.","id":"67da-f071-2629-4887","parent_id":"d195-aeb8-2400-484b","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"task","title":"Route plan-authoring guidance to authors + fix stale gate-doc thresholds"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784085066561220001,"uuid":"44e31403-e683-4127-ae96-a31715132747"}